Executive Profile
William G. Bardel  Associate Headmaster and Chief Financial Officer, Lawrenceville SchoolAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships78--
Background

		Mr. William G. Bardel served as Associate Headmaster and Chief Financial Officer of the Lawrenceville School, a preparatory high school in Lawrenceville, New Jersey, from 1994 to 2006. Mr. Bardel served as the Head of the Government Advisory Group of Lehman Brothers in London, England from 1988 to 1994, which provided financial market guidance to developing nations in Africa, Asia, Eastern Europe, South America and the Middle East. He has acted as a financial consultant ... to a number of educational institutions since 2006. From 1984 to 1994, Mr. Bardel served as a managing director of Lehman Brothers. He has been a Director of Black Stone Minerals GP LLC at Black Stone Minerals, L.P. since March 2015. He serves as a Director at Hudson City, MHC. He has served as director of BSNR since 2004. He served as a Director of Hudson City Bancorp, Inc. since 2003 and served as its Lead Independent Director. He served as a Director of Hudson City Savings Bank, FSB. Mr. Bardel is a graduate of Yale University, he has a Master's degree from Oxford University where he was a Rhodes Scholar. He holds a J.D. degree from Harvard Law School.Read Full Background




